<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5828936>
    dc:description "Fig. 6. A–F. Kainomyces isomali Thaxt. A–B. Mature thalli showing the rostrum (ro) on the perithecia. C. Detail of an immature perithecium showing numerous wall cells for each row and the subterminal outgrowth on the perithecium. D. Detail of basal area of perithecium showing brown spots. E. Detail of receptacle with antheridia (an). F. Detail of the lower receptacle showing comb-like pigmentation. – G. Hydrophilomyces atroseptatus T.Majewski. Young thallus where darkened septa on the base of secondary branchlets are arrowed. Scale bars: A–B, F–G = 50 µm; C–E = 20 µm. Photographs from slides ZMUC C-F-124250 (A), ZMUC C-F-124252 (B), ZMUC C-F-124002 (C–F), and ZMUC C-F- 123693 (G)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5828936/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

